iovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Immune Zinc Size Size 60 tablets 120 tablets Good health changes everything - support everyday wellness with Blackmores Immune Zinc. This daily formula combines zinc and vitamin A to help maintain immune system health, support healthy immune system function, and support the immune system to fight illness. It also contributes to skin integrity, wound healing, and general health and wellbeing. Zinc is essential for reproductive system health and plays a role in maintaining sperm health. With added antioxidant action to reduce free radicals formed in the body, Blackmores Immune Zinc also helps maintain skin health, nail strength, and hair health. Taken daily, it supports the body’s natural defences and promotes healthy skin repair. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Immune System Health Skin Health Reproductive Health No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Supports immune system health. Supports healthy immune system function. Supports immune system to fight illness. Reduces free radicals in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Supports hair health. Supports nail health/strength/thickness. Maintains reproductive system health and sperm health. Maintains skin health and skin integrity/structure. Maintains wound healing. Dosage Adults 19 years and older Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING: If you are considering becoming pregnant, are pregnant, or are breastfeeding, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. WARNING: When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents Vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol equivalents for men. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible. (Contains vitamin B6). If symptoms persist talk to your healthcare professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites, phenylalanine and soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Supports immune system health. Supports healthy immune system function. Supports immune system to fight illness. Reduces free radicals in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Supports hair health. Supports nail health/strength/thickness. Maintains reproductive system health and sperm health. Maintains skin health and skin integrity/structure. Maintains wound healing. Adults 19 years and older Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. WARNING: If you are considering becoming pregnant, are pregnant, or are breastfeeding, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. WARNING: When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents Vitamin A can cause birth defects. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol equivalents for men. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible. (Contains vitamin B6). If symptoms persist talk to your healthcare professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites, phenylalanine and soya bean products. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Retinol acetate 860 micrograms equivalent vitamin A 2500 IU 750 micrograms retinol equivalents Pyridoxine hydrochloride 50 mg equivalent pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 41.1 mg Zinc amino acid chelate 74.5 mg equivalent zinc 14.9 mg Manganese amino acid chelate 20 mg equivalent manganese 2 mg Magnesium phosphate pentahydrate 90 mg equivalent magnesium 18.6 mg Show More Immune Zinc Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Prac