:"783b46dc-be55-55a9-bc43-6a15a1bfdb80"},{"name":"Vitamin A","unit":"mcg","amount":750,"itemType":"supplement","sourceUrl":null,"confidence":"high","sourceText":null,"servingLabel":null,"supplementId":"df05c30c-144e-5d03-92dc-c895f7cb00c4"},{"name":"Vitamin B6","unit":"mg","amount":41.1,"itemType":"supplement","sourceUrl":null,"confidence":"high","sourceText":null,"servingLabel":null,"supplementId":"ccc3e67b-d753-5315-a8cb-a8aefa8b2fd8"}]'::jsonb, '{"dosage":"for use. Read the","locale":"en","parser":"blackmores_structured_ingredients_v2","titleEn":"Blackmores Bio Zinc","htmlLength":173899,"description":"Blackmores Bio Zinc tablets supporting skin health and immune function.","descriptionEn":"Blackmores Bio Zinc tablets supporting skin health and immune function.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Bio Zinc Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Bio Zinc Size Size 84 tablets 168 tablets Blackmores Bio Zinc is a one-a-day formula combining zinc with key nutrients. It supports skin health, supports immune system health, and supports reproductive system health. It also supports wound healing and supports general health and wellbeing. Good health changes everything - support your skin and immune health with Blackmores Bio Zinc. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Wound Healing Skin Health Immune System Health No Added Gluten No Added Yeast No Added Soya Bean No Added Dairy No Added Wheat Benefits & How To Use Benefits Maintains healthy skin and collagen formation. Supports skin integrity and wound healing. Maintains healthy immune system function. Supports healthy sperm and motility. Maintains reproductive system health. High strength, one-a-day dose. Contains a form of zinc chelate which is well tolerated. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding talk to your health professional before use. WARNING - When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, vitamin A can cause birth defects. If you are pregnant or considering becoming pregnant, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol for men. WARNING - stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible. [Contains vitamin B6]. Dietary supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. If you have pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Maintains healthy skin and collagen formation. Supports skin integrity and wound healing. Maintains healthy immune system function. Supports healthy sperm and motility. Maintains reproductive system health. High strength, one-a-day dose. Contains a form of zinc chelate which is well tolerated. Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding talk to your health professional before use. WARNING - When taken in excess of 3000 micrograms retinol equivalents, vitamin A can cause birth defects. If you are pregnant or considering becoming pregnant, do not take Vitamin A supplements without consulting your doctor or pharmacist. The recommended daily amount of Vitamin A from all sources is 700 micrograms retinol equivalents for women and 900 micrograms retinol for men. WARNING - stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible. [Contains vitamin B6]. Dietary supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. If you have pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients