butes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress. Vitamin C contributes to normal collagen formation for the normal function of skin. Vitamin C contributes to the normal function of the immune system. Vitamin C contributes to normal energy yielding metabolism.","description":"Support radiant skin and collagen production with Vitamin C by Swisse. Ideal for beauty-conscious consumers in Thailand.","priceAmount":590,"descriptionEn":"Supports skin collagen formation, immune function, energy metabolism and protection from oxidative stress with 1000 mg Vitamin C per serving.","descriptionTh":"สนับสนุนการสร้างคอลลาเจนของผิว ระบบภูมิคุ้มกัน เมตาบอลิซึมของพลังงาน และป้องกันความเครียดออกซิเดชัน ด้วยวิตามินซี 1000 มก. ต่อหน่วยบริโภค","extractedText":"Swisse Vitamin C - Swisse Thailand Skip to content Products Back Products Beauty Eye Care Gummies Gut Health Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Moisturisers Multivitamins Serums Skin Super Fruits & Herbs All Products Range Wellness Beauty Skincare About Back Our Story Ingredients Wellness Hub Sign in Search Cart (0) Cart empty Your cart is empty Continue shopping     svg]:w-full group-hover:text-uiGrey\"> Home / Vitamin C   Skip to product information Open media 1 in modal Open media 2 in modal Open media 3 in modal Swisse Vitamin C Swisse Vitamin C 1000 mg Premium Formula is designed to nourish and restore health. It can be taken daily and reduces stomach irritation with a non-acidic formula from Calcium Ascorbate. Swisse committed to contributing positively to the needs of society and the planet, and we are the carbon neutral company. #VitaminC #NonAcidic Sale price 590 ฿ Where to buy Buy at TikTok Buy at Shopee Buy at Lazada Buy at Line Benefits Vitamin C contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress. Vitamin C contributes to normal collagen formation for the normal function of skin. Vitamin C contributes to the normal function of the immune system. Vitamin C contributes to normal energy yielding metabolism. Key Ingredients Vitamin C 1000 mg Directions and Warnings DIRECTIONS: 1 -2 tablets daily. Take after a meal, or as directed by a healthcare professional. WARNINGS: Children, and pregnant women should not consume. Should eat a variety of the five categories of food in appropriate proportions STORAGE: Store below 25C, in a cool, dry place. Do not use, if cap seal is broken. Reasons to love us We have been developing science-based formulas using premium ingredients sourced from around the world for over 50 years. We believe in natural ingredients being our hero ingredients. We also pursue the latest research findings to formulate our advanced product ranges and consistently strive to anticipate consumer demand. Backed by science Premium quality formula 50+ year heritage Certified B-Corp We are B-Corp Certified B Corps are for-profit companies that meet high standards of social and environmental performance, transparency, and accountability. Swisse is a brand of H&H Group, a certified B Corp. We feel honoured to be part of a global community using business as a force for good. Frequently Asked Questions Do we need to take vitamin supplements? The key is to ensure that we get a complete and balanced intake of nutrients each day. However, due to lifestyle limitations and dietary choices, we may not always receive the necessary nutrients in adequate amounts. In such cases, dietary supplements can be beneficial. Can Swisse products be taken alongside medication or medical treatments? Each individual has different nutritional and medicinal needs. If you are unsure whether Swisse products are suitable for you, it is best to consult a doctor. Please note that dietary supplements do not prevent, alter, or replace medical treatment or a well-balanced diet. What is the best time to take vitamins? Some supplements work best when taken with food, while others are more effective on an empty stomach. It is essential to follow the instructions on the label to maximize the benefits of each product. How long do dietary supplements last? In general, dietary supplements have a shelf life of approximately two years from the manufacturing date. Where does Swisse source its ingredients? We carefully select and source high-quality, premium-grade ingredients from around the world to ensure that only the best components go into our products. Where are Swisse products manufactured? Most of our products are manufactured in Australia. Please refer to the product packaging for the specific country of origin. The recommended dosage on the label applies to which age group? The recommended dosage is intended for individuals aged 18 and above. You may also like Swisse C Acerola Plus Sale price 690 ฿ Swisse Collagen + Grape Seed Sale price 840 ฿ Swisse Astaxanthin + Gluta Sale price 1,250 ฿ Swisse Grape Seed Sale price 690 ฿ Swisse HSN+ Sale price 650 ฿ Swisse Sunneday Sale price 1,450 ฿ Our Products Beauty Eye Care Gut Health Gummies Immunity Joints, Bones, & Muscles Multivitamins Super Fruits & Herbs Skincare About Swisse Our Story Ingredients Help & Support FAQs Contact Us Privacy Policy Follow Us &copy; Swisse Thailand , 2026 Choosing a selection results in a full page refresh.\n\nBenefits Vitamin C contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress. Vitamin C contributes to normal collagen formation for the normal function of skin. Vitamin C contributes to the normal function of the immune system. Vitamin C contributes to normal energy yielding metabolism.\n\nKey Ingredients Vitamin C 1000 mg\n\nDirections and Warnings DIRECTIONS: 1 -2 tablets daily. Take after a meal, or as directed by a healthcare professional.","productOffers":[{"url":"https://vt.tiktok.com/ZMBa1GBYF/?page=TikTokShop","label":"Buy at TikTok","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"direct","platform":"tiktok","priority":100},{"url":"https://shopee.co.th/swisse_thailand","label":"Buy at Shopee","status":"active","network":"swisse_where_to_buy","linkType":"dir