ll production, support energy production and a healthy pregnancy. Ideal for those looking for a gentle and well-absorbed iron option. Good health changes everything—support your iron needs with Blackmores. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Women&#x27;s Health Pregnancy Health Energy No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Gentle on the digestive system and a lower constipation, low nausea, bioavailable form of iron when taken with food. Supports a healthy pregnancy and maternal health when dietary intake is inadequate. Maintains healthy iron levels in the body when dietary intake is inadequate. Assists healthy red blood cell production and oxygen transport to body tissues when dietary intake is inadequate. Supports energy production when iron levels are low. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Not for the treatment of iron deficiency conditions. If you are concerned about the health of your baby, talk to your health professional. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Gentle on the digestive system and a lower constipation, low nausea, bioavailable form of iron when taken with food. Supports a healthy pregnancy and maternal health when dietary intake is inadequate. Maintains healthy iron levels in the body when dietary intake is inadequate. Assists healthy red blood cell production and oxygen transport to body tissues when dietary intake is inadequate. Supports energy production when iron levels are low. Adults Take 1 tablet a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Not for the treatment of iron deficiency conditions. If you are concerned about the health of your baby, talk to your health professional. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. Supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications, always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Iron (II) glycinate 87.7 mg equivalent iron 24 mg Women&#x27;s Premium Iron Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Kore